The paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning systems in wearable sensor systems to adversarial attacks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The study also involves human activity recognition (HAR) as an example sensor system, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of sensor data in HAR suggests a possible connection to computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
